   <h3><u>When creating a notice on the Indian Army website, there are several important pieces of information that should be included. Here is a detailed guide on what to write on the notice page:</h3></u><br>     
                             "https://www.joinindiannavy.gov.in"    <br>
<p>
1. Title: Begin by giving a clear and concise title to the notice. Use keywords that accurately reflect the content of the notice. For example, if it pertains to recruitment, you could use a title like "Indian Army Recruitment Notice - [Year]".<br><br>

2. Date: Clearly state the date when the notice is being published. It helps users in understanding the relevance and recency of the information<br><br>

3. Introduction: Provide a brief introduction or opening statement that captures the attention of the readers and gives them a general overview of the notice's purpose. Mention the importance or significance of the notice.<br><br><br>

4. Content: Present the notice's content in a well-structured format. Use paragraphs, headings, and bullet points as necessary to enhance readability. Here are some key points that may be included:a. Recruitment Notices: If the notice is related to recruitment, provide details about the position, eligibility criteria, application process, and any accompanying documents needed.<br>

   b. Training or Examination Notices: In case the notice is about training programs or examinations, include information about the dates, venues, registration procedures, and any prerequisites.<br>

   c. Promotions or Transfers: If the notice is regarding promotions or transfers within the army, outline the eligibility criteria, requirements, and timelines.<br>

   d. Events or Celebrations: When announcing events or celebrations, include dates, location, and details about the program, including any participation guidelines or registration procedures.<br>

  e.Important Instructions: Include any significant instructions or guidelines that need to be followed by the intended audience. This could include deadlines, document submission procedures, or specific requirements.<br><br>

  f. Contact Information: Provide contact details or a helpline number where individuals can seek clarification or further information regarding the notice.<br><br>

5. Closing: End the notice with a closing statement, such as "For any further queries, contact the provided helpline" or "Stay connected for future updates."
<br><br>
6. Signature: Add the name, designation, and contact information of the authorized person who is responsible for the notice.<br>
</p>
